Usage:
    universal-pause [options]

Universal pause for Linux games. Allows you to pause non-pausable cutscenes
and games. You can bind the command to a key and use it at the right moment

Options:
    -h, --help      Print this message and exit
    -r, --run       Pause/unpause the active X-server window.
                    WARNING! Can freeze the terminal emulator process
    -s, --silent    Disable terminal output
    -v, --volume    Set the volume (0.1 by default)
    -f, --evfind    Find the input device
    -t, --evtest    Test the input device events (evdev).
                    Specify a path to test a specific device
    --version       Print the version and exit

